<p>
	<br />
	Cedarwood essential oil is one of the oldest aromatics out there and is still available today. The oil has been used ever since the Egyptians ruled the world thousands of years ago. They used it to treat any problem they had with their skin, whether it be dry from the heat or in need of soothing, they enjoyed it as they believed it gave a fresh glow to their skin tone.</p>
<p>
	The <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Cedarwood-Essential-Oil-Cedrus-Virginiana/">Cedarwood oil</a> is still used today to treat a variety of skin conditions, including itchy skin, acne, oily skin and many issues with the scalp. The essential oil is well known for its soothing qualities when applied to the skin and is often used to help in the treatment of cystitis.</p>
<p>
	The Cedarwood oil gives off an earthly, woody aroma which provides a calming influence on both the body and the mind. When it is used in a vaporiser or a burner, the aromatic qualities of the oil can help with arthritis, bronchitis and respiratory problems. It can clear the chest and aid breathing along with filling your home with a comforting scent, getting rid of any nasty, unwanted odours.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Cedarwood oil can be mixed with various other essential oils to create more useful or bespoke blends depending on what is needed. When it is mixed with <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Citronella-Essential-Oil-Cymbopogon-Nardus/">citronella</a>, the oils combine to create a very potent insect repellent. In general the Cedarwood essential oil will blend well with a wide variety of wood based essential oils, to create pleasing aromas and calming environments. As well as the wood based oils, Cedarwood will blend well with <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Benzoin-Essential-Oil-Styrax-Benzoin/">Benzoin</a>, <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Cypress-Essential-Oil-Cupressus-Sempervirens/">Cypress</a>, <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Juniper-Berry-Essential-Oil-Juniperus-communis/">Juniper</a> and <a href="http://www.avena.co.uk/Melissa-Lemon-Balm-Essential-Oil/">Melissa</a>, creating exciting and useful oil blends.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Feel the benefits of cedarwood oil, it really is a versitile and useful oil to have in yout cabinet. Remember when applying essential oil to the skin, always dilute the essential oil with a carrier oil for safety.&nbsp;</p>
